2.3 Definition of a Nondegenerate Solution
We say that this problem has a nondegenerate solution if, as the number of
remaining periods of life gets arbitrarily large, the backward-iterating solution
defines a unique limiting consumption function c(â€¢) that satisfies
0 < c(m) < âˆ

