x, y, and z as examples of z-bounded functions; and using 0(m) = 0 to indicate
the function that returns zero for any argument, Boyd (1990) proves the following.
Boydâ€™s Weighted Contraction Mapping Theorem. Let T : Cz (A, B) â†’
